<DOC><DOCNO> AP900327-0084 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-03-27-90 1230EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-Panama-Cuba     03-27 0151</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Panama-Cuba,0155</SECOND><HEAD>Expelled Cuban Ambassador Leaves Panama</HEAD><DATELINE>PANAMA CITY, Panama (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The Cuban ambassador to Panama hasreturned home after being expelled from the country because of hisgovernment's refusal to recognize the Panamanian government.   Lazaro Mora Segade, his wife and three companions left on a Cubade Aviacion flight late Monday night.   Diplomats from the Dominican Republic and Ecuador were on handto see him off. The ambassador did not speak to reporters nor allowthem to take his photograph.   Airport officials who asked not to be named said the ambassadortook 80 suitcases and two pets with him.   Cuba has refused to recognize the civilian government installedin Panama after the U.S. invasion in December that ousted militaryleader Manuel Antonio Noriega. The Cuban Embassy in Panama Citygave refuge to Noriega's family for awhile after the invasion.   Noriega is in Miami awaiting trial on drug charges.</TEXT></DOC>